troduction by Douglas R. Hofstadter, this book will appeal students, scholars, and professionals in the fields of mathematics, computer science, logic and philosophy, and science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aGödel's theorem. 7aMATHEMATICS / Logic.2bisacsh1 aHofstadter, Douglas R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewman, James R., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814759035.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814759035423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814759035/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles